<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 4:51PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Beaverhead County through 515 PM MDT...
At 450 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Spencer, or 9 miles west of Idmon, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lakeview.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
